

## What I Built & Learned

During this IoT assignment, I gained practical experience by designing and simulating different ESP32-based projects using Wokwi. Each project focused on collecting sensor data, processing it, and taking suitable actions automatically. Working on these projects improved my understanding of how IoT systems operate in real-life situations.

One of the projects I completed was a **Smart Greenhouse Automation System**. In this project, I used a DHT22 sensor to measure temperature and humidity, while an LDR sensor detected the surrounding light level. Depending on the sensor readings, LEDs were used to represent devices such as a cooling fan, heater, and grow light. I also implemented averaging of sensor values to reduce fluctuations and obtain more stable readings. This project taught me the importance of maintaining suitable environmental conditions for healthy plant growth through automation.

Another project was a **River Water Level Monitoring System**. An ultrasonic sensor was used to calculate the distance between the sensor and the water surface. Based on the measured value, the system identified whether the water level was safe, approaching danger, or critical. LEDs and a buzzer provided different warning indications for each condition. While developing this project, I learned how IoT can be used to monitor natural resources and provide early warnings during emergencies.

I also worked on a **Heart Rate and Oxygen Monitoring Simulation**. Since a medical sensor was not available in the simulation, an LDR was used to generate sample readings. The program calculated average values to reduce sudden changes and displayed the processed results on the Serial Monitor. Alerts were generated whenever the simulated heart rate or oxygen level moved outside the normal range. This project gave me an understanding of how wearable health monitoring systems analyze sensor data before generating alerts.

Throughout these activities, I developed several important IoT skills, including sensor interfacing, writing efficient Arduino code, implementing decision-making logic, reducing noisy sensor readings, troubleshooting simulation errors, and testing projects in a virtual environment before real hardware implementation.

## Application of IoT Skills

These projects showed me that IoT technology has applications in many areas such as agriculture, healthcare, disaster management, and smart homes. I learned how to design systems that continuously monitor their surroundings and respond automatically without human intervention.

The assignment also strengthened my programming, debugging, and problem-solving abilities. I am now more confident in connecting different sensors with ESP32, interpreting sensor data, and creating intelligent systems that can improve safety, comfort, and efficiency. These skills will be valuable for future engineering projects as well as professional work in automation and embedded systems.

# My Future IoT Project Idea

## Smart Indoor Air Quality & Comfort Monitor

### Components

* ESP32 Microcontroller
* DHT22 Temperature and Humidity Sensor
* MQ-135 Air Quality Sensor
* LDR Sensor
* OLED Display
* Buzzer and LEDs
* Wi-Fi Connectivity

### Working

The proposed system will continuously monitor indoor temperature, humidity, air quality, and lighting conditions. The ESP32 will process the collected data and compare it with predefined comfort limits. If the air quality becomes poor, the system will activate a buzzer and recommend opening windows or switching on ventilation. If the room is too hot or too cold, it will suggest using a fan or heater. Similarly, low light intensity will trigger a lighting recommendation.

The collected data will also be uploaded to a cloud platform using MQTT or HTTP so that users can check room conditions remotely through a mobile phone or web dashboard. Historical data can help users identify trends and improve indoor comfort while reducing unnecessary energy consumption.

### Applications

This project can be used in homes, offices, schools, libraries, and hospitals to maintain a healthy indoor environment. It can improve comfort, support better health, and encourage energy-efficient use of electrical appliances. It also demonstrates how IoT technology can create smarter and more sustainable living spaces.
